Yes, long term I absolutely agree about the organic woody feel. Given that we already have walls and ceiling in untreated plywood I think the rest of the interior should follow the same overall theme, contrasted with some color in certain places and a plant or two. With a strongly contrasting floor as suggested above.

This metal suggestion is mainly to get something operational quickly + that we relieve the yellow container of current clutter. Once we get a storage container (I'm working on it) then we can opt for your suggestion of a more minimalistic setup. 

I don't think we should store so much in the house though. Much better to find containerized solutions.

@elch has an existing system for storing 3D printing material in a heated closet which also contains the Bitcoin miner. That unit will have to be in the container anyway since it provides the overall heating. 

@spargeltarzan Great! Will let you know. We have an existing Kärcher vac which will probably do the job. You can check out the exact model in the Tau storage room. It's superfluous there anyway when we have the high quality Blue Bosch model in the woodshop.

Hej all.
At the last tau meeting which was hijacked by Frihamnstorget we decided to set the last Friday of everymonth as a building day at Frihamnstorget.

This is the day when most of us with projects there will be working out there and being communal and co-creating and all that lovely jazz while collectively working with the goal to make Frihamnstorget as a whole an epic place that can live for many more years.
So check your calendar, and maybe there is something you want to do there.
last Friday of the month. We start at 9:30  for a full day of creation, cleaning and good vibes.

So our first event will be in the 27th of March.  
